message:
Add keywords, and use them for kwargs syntax

Use .. instead of / for qualified symbols

Spell out lambdas and use \ instead of # for reader macros,
for better emacs compatibility (Python has no char type.)

Add TODOs to readme

update rough draft
Allow stacked reader macros without whitespace
Bake in basic reader macros ,@ ' ` , without \
Implement automatic qualification of symbols in template quote
Add more compilation documentation to the TODOs in the README
Clarify how to transpile multiple modules in a package

Cleanup README

Add Table of Contents

Change reader macro syntax to use a trailing backslash instead

Update readme for new reader macro syntax
Add more syntax highlighting to README
Rework README and make doctests pass

Update no-default kwonly example from : to :_

Add some lambda commentary
Implement tests for Hissp REPL examples in documentation

Change `pydocstring` fences back to `python` for GitHub compatibility

It's too bad they can't support the same markdown.
Fix doctests. Fill in Macros section more.

Change :_ to :? everywhere.

It actually was :? originally.
I tried it with :_ and ultimately didn't like the change.

Change reader macro character to ``#``

The ``\`` was confusing Emacs.

Fix issue with compile-time local imports

And update tests for it.
A macro may use a variable from the same module later.
Allow ``xAUTO..._`` to match any number in document tests
Final cleanup for PyPI package release.

Add badges

The Gitter badger was supposed to badge the readme.
It forked the repo, but that's it. No branch, no push, no PR.
Bad badger. I'll badge it myself.

I'm also adding the readthedocs badge.

Remove contributing section

Including the TOC.

Pickle in text mode by default
Special-case Ellipsis compilation
Speed up some Hypothesis tests

Binary strings are represented as text in the compiled output,
so binary mode is not actually smaller.
Text mode is also more human-readable.

Pretty-print collection literals in compiled output

And bump required Python version to 3.8+

Readme update

Change to "control word" terminology to match Hebigo,
and avoid confusion with Python keywords.
Add method call syntax trick for macroexpand to FAQ
fix some faulty markup in README.md for sybil tests
Move README FAQ to Sphinx docs
Add (-):issp logo to index.rst and README.md
Update docs for improved REPL continuation handling
Use a two space indent in Hebigo example
Clarify initial reference to "Lissp" in README.md

Force utf8 encoding of README.md when read in setup.py

And add em dashes.
Improve compiler's indentation of multiline paired arguments

Apply suggestions from code review

Fix typo in macro tutorial.
Make docstring in README example consistent with source.

Update README.md

fix parentheses for the example with Hebigo macros in Lissp

Rename macros module
Import utilities into package level
Add interact wrapper utility
Add link comments in temperature app

Eliminate attrgetter- @# overload

Use X#X.foo.etc instead. It's only two more characters, the same as get#.

Update comma style for readerless

I developed this style after attempting to write about a page of code in readerless. Putting the commas at the start of the line instead improved readability quite a bit.
